Iron March Charter and Mission Statement

Official Iron March Flag

 

Iron March Mission Statement

 

Iron March is a global online fascist community that seeks to become the Forge of the 21st Century Fascist by establishing an online Fascist Space so as to foster and develop internet resources dedicated to the study, understanding and practice of the Fascist Worldview and Lifestyle; and a global Fascist Fraternity in the world for the purpose of creating a non-movement/party form of association between fascists that can in turn lead to the strengthening of existing or formation of new movements that engage in our common struggle worldwide.

Iron March itself is not a movement and never intends to become one, rather it is the platform for the creation of the global Fascist Fraternity and the central communications hub for its members online as well as the HQ for the online Fascist Space and the primary source for studying our worldview, thus acting as the Fascist Alma Mater.

Furthermore, a distinction must be made that Iron March and Iron March forum (i.e. IRONMARCH.ORG) are not synonymous as the intent and ambitions outlined in this Mission Statement clearly show that Iron March has outgrown itself as just an internet forum, now encompassing an array of both online and real world activities and goals, making Iron March a living community while the Iron March forum acts as its online HQ. 

To further explain our intentions each key term mentioned above is explained below:

  • Forge(-ing) of the 21st Century Fascist - the most broad and succinct way of describing our Mission Statement that covers both our online and real world activities, implying that we seeks to create not just mere political and career/hobbyist fascists but rather people who share an inherently different perception of the world and thus live and breathe Fascism 24/7, making it not just a mere ideology but a Worldview and Way of Life or Lifestyle, that in the Modern World would appear as a form of counter-culture.
     
  • Fascist Alma Mater - the role that the Iron March forum plays in educating people towards a more comprehensive understanding of the Fascist Struggle and Worldview, and a common way of referring to any Iron March projects dedicated to further research and education in those fields (ex. Fascist Archive, Antimony Group).
     
  • Fascist Space - common way of referring to all online Iron March projects and online projects/activities created by members of the IM community that in any way further our goals, including educational, creative, demonstrative outlets of the Fascist Lifestyle (ex. NOOSE). The Iron Pride Network is the formal name of this space. 
     
  • Fascist Fraternity - Iron March community manifested in the real world as a means of fascist association that exists outside belonging to any particular movement or party, encouraging fascists to spend time together outside of movement activities or to the contrary bring together fascists with no existing affiliations, to share in common interests or form some organization of their own. It is important to note that in the event of a movement's formation Iron March has no direct control over it and can merely offer advice as a community, in the hopes of nurturing the growth of a successful and dedicated fascist organization.

Most of the planning behind the aforementioned goals and projects occurs on our online HQ - the Iron March forum. As such the Forum Charter in no small part defines the nature of our community and can be used not as only a guide for using the forum itself but also as a point of reference to the standards of our community at large.

Honour Truth - Wage War - Have Fun

 

Official Iron March Crest

 

Iron March Forum Charter
 

I. Adminship

The Adminship are the Iron March Forum Admins, tasked with maintaining the forum, disciplinary actions, enforcing the values of our worldview and the planning of all IM projects to further our common goals.

The official symbol of the Adminship and the Iron March forum is the Machina Hierarchia - Hierarchy Machine (cog and hands) - it symbolizes the organic unity that exists in a proper hierarchy, making it work as smoothly and efficiently as a machine; alternatively it symbolizes the fostering of an organic unity from what were initially mechanical means.

II. Black Corps

The Black Corps are the Iron March Forum Moderators - the most trusted and true who embody both the values that are at the foundation of this community and of the values of our worldview. The Black Corps are tasked with maintaining order and cleanliness on the forum, as well as seeking out and purging unwanted elements as outlined in segment III of this charter (Community). 

To become a member of the Black Corps one must be a long term member of the IM Forum in good standing who has also proven to be responsible and thus worthy of the title and the tasks that come with it.

III. Community

Iron March is not a movement, but we expect users to share our purpose – to take an active interest in using the forum, and when contributing to do so as fascists in ultimate pursuit of knowledge, ideas, contacts, etcetera. Those who are not constructive and threaten this are in the wrong place and unwelcome. We recognize there is a widespread character issue in movement politics, and we start here to address some of those problems here. The following rules are to be observed by all members and handled quickly and diplomatically where possible.

1. No ‘Sperging’. As in ‘Asperger’s syndrome’, an Autistic mental disorder characterized by extreme egocentricity and an inability to understand how to interact socially. This policy is to curtail and recognize the tendencies of users whose actions and motivations are outside our common goals, are deliberately of no benefit to anyone, and only serve to cause trouble. Regardless of whether it is motivated by narcissism, social alienation, cowardice, or stupidity we must control it, and it is the user’s responsibility to observe these following principles which will serve as a guide to ensure there will be no problems for you while you are here.

1.1 - Role-playing. The tendency to portray personal views in the third person with no clear relation to the real world constitutes a form of role-playing. Another form of role-playing is found in arrogance; insisting on special treatment or to be regarded as a separate tier, in contradiction to the fact it is usually marked by an absence of; personal effort, courage, commitment, consistency, positions that will attract negative response, interest in people, etc - by coincidence. If you are a fake you will be recognized and publicly called out.

1.2 - Fashion Fascism. Fascism isn't a fetish – if you regularly treat it as such your motivations will be questioned as ulterior. If you reflect your political ‘identity’ in things like science fiction or anything else found in Television, Video games, hobbies, sub-cultures etc, it tells us that you are unable to distinguish between the two.

1.3 - Shitposting. Making shit posts; this happens when a post is devoid of content or context, eg randomly responding with a reaction image. If you have nothing else to contribute you have no right to be engaging in this.

1.4 - Constructive debate. The goal of debate is the pursuit of truth therefore you should take care about what you are saying and care about opposing arguments and should assume it is the same for your opponent – so where relevant you should be capable of providing sources to back up an opinion - this is an argument. Ignoring responses while continuing to argue shows you have no investment in the discussion and also, that you have nothing to offer or contribute.

1.5 - Conduct. It is your responsibility to judge group relations and know what not to post and where things should be posted. When you can participate in a forum drama, promote yourself, become insolent towards members, etc, is something only you can judge.

If these are not monitored by the user and kept in check it may result in messages of warning from moderators.

2. This is not Stormfront. Our community is based on discussion and debate constructive towards fascist goals, it is not a hangout for White Nationalists and their unique subculture. Stormfront and VNN forums already provide this in terms of its endless topics on conspiracy theories, chimpouts, Zionism, etcetera. Exclusively posting remarks and threads of that nature without proper context is a form of spamming.

Likewise, we are not a New Right intellectual circle jerk and we do not tolerate aimless, abstract philosophizing and the typical self-important snobbish behavior that comes with it. Furthermore we recognize displays of such behavior to be a form of violation of points outlined in segment III of this charter (Community).

3. Tolerance. We accept people with strong viewpoints even if ultimately we seek everyone to join us in our comprehension of the world, whilst also understanding that this can be accomplished only so far via our internet forum platform. Those who take themselves too seriously yet refuse to debate become paranoid, patronizing, passive aggressive and can become the source of drama. Users of non straight-white-male-fascist backgrounds also need to be conscious of their differences and check their privilege at the door. If you have allowed yourself to become aggravated through your own fault we will not side with you and you may be held responsible.

4. Sophian Language. You are expected to use this website with intelligence, knowing what not to write and to read between the lines. By posting here you need to personally be prepared it might be read in a court, quoted on in a newspaper, or read to your weeping mother – and hold yourself to account. Don't ask us to delete all your posts because you have "changed your mind.", or even attempt to alter them yourself. Remember, your public posts are cached by search engines or may be recorded by others.

5. Untermenschen. Just being you can result in an immediate ban, and we will take immediate and permanent action if it is ever found out the following applies to you.

5.1 - We do not allow or entertain the mentally ill to the extent they cannot understand fascism, (for instance those who do genuinely suffer from Autism) and it is our responsibility to direct them away from this place because they should not be here.

5.2 - Expression of interest in Paedophilia (Including any similar inclinations towards the under-aged) will result immediate ban, and even the slightest hint will be treated seriously.

5.3 - Simply put, we reserve the right to ban you if you are any kind of faggot. If you feel the need to tell the world then you will bring the consequences on yourself just as hard. Belonging to the furry fandom is prohibited, partly because it also involves a breach of 1.1 and 1.2, but mostly because it is utterly degenerative (it deserves note here because it will apply even if explicitly sexual grounds cannot be ascertained).

Failure to comply may result in internment, when a member's activity on the forum is restricted to the Showers. These members will be marked as Prisoners and they will inevitably be Gassed.

IV. Forum Activities

Iron March Forum provides it's users with a number of activities that help us develop as a forum, an information center and a community for fellow fascists as well as establish new projects outside the Forum both online and in real life. Any user can officially sign up for any such activity and become an active contributor. Simply follow the rules of each such activity and you will find yourself occupied with interesting projects that will help you develop your skills or further your knowledge.

V. Discipline

We expect every user to follow the rules set forth by the Adminship.

1. Our community is interested in active members, not lurkers and defunct profiles. All accounts that have zero posts for a week after registry on the forum will be deleted. At least once a year (sometime in January) the forum undergoes a purge of defunct profiles, meaning profiles that have been inactive for a period of one year will be are permanently deleted. Profiles with large post counts will be spared, however the minimum post count required to avoid account deletion increases over time. 

2. Before creating a new topic make sure that a similar one doesn't already exist and be sure to post topics in the appropriate sections of the Iron March forum. Use the search bar in the top right corner if  you are not sure where to look.

3. Do not derail topics, do not flame, do not spam.

*It is the user’s responsibility not to be trolled.

4. Follow the respective rules of all forum activities and projects as they are explained in the sections dedicated to those activities.

5. Moderators and Admins may dispense punishment at their discretion and can give formal warnings to users who behave in an unacceptable manner (unnecessary aggression, blatant and systematic disregard of the forum rules and etc). Punishments vary from preliminary warnings and temporary suspension to immediate gassings with no warning at all. 

VI. Uniform

1. Forum avatars are restricted to a size of 160x160 pixels, and 50 kb.

2. Forum signatures are restricted to one image of 800x140 pixels and 5 lines of text.

3. Admins can be recognized by the symbol of the Iron March Adminship below their title and avatar - Machina Hierarchia and Admins Wreath.

4. Members of the Black Corps can be recognized by the symbol of the Black Corps below their title and avatar - the Sword and Shield, combined with the Machina Hierarchia. Black Corps Captain is recognized by the same symbol with wings.

5. Users are discouraged from taking the names of historic persons, eg ‘Benito Mussolini’, and may be asked to change their username.
 

Follow these rules diligently, least you face the wrath of the Adminship.

Gas the Kikes, Race War Now! 1488 Boots on the Ground!

When enabled, the entire page output will be cached so if more than one guest is viewing the site, each page only needs to be generated once which can significantly decrease the resource usage of your site if you have lots of guests online at the same time.
The longer you cache pages for, the less often the cache will need to be refreshed (so less resources will be used) but the longer it will take for your site to be updated with the latest content. When a cached page is being shown, view counters also won't be updated.
If your site rarely has many guests online at the same time, it may take more resources to store the cache than is saved by it and so it may be better to disable it.
If you have a caching method configured that will be used, otherwise the cache is stored in the database.

For many blocks, getting the data every time the block needs to be shown can be bad for performance. This setting allows you to only reload the block after a set period of time.
This means there will be a delay before the content of blocks is changed - for example, if you set this to 5 minutes, and you have a block showing the most recent topics, it may take up to 5 minutes for a new topic to show.

Computer programs known as spam bots may attempt to register on your site to post unwanted content. CAPTCHA is a test designed to be simple for humans to answer correctly, but difficult for computer programs. The selected CAPTCHA type will display on the registration form of your site and will need to be completed successfully in order to register an account.

The user usually only needs to check a box and the system intelligently detects if the user is human. The user may be shown two distorted words and asked to type the displayed words if the system cannot accurately determine if they are a human. More Information

Disabling CAPTCHA will put your site at a significant risk to spam. Enabling a CAPTCHA type is strongly recommended.

Friendly URLs are URLs that a human can look at and understand, as opposed to what may appear as an obscure string of text.
In addition to being more understandable to users, they help search engines understand better what is on each page.
It is strongly recommended to use friendly URLs as they are easier for both humans and search engine spiders to understand.

When enabled, Friendly URLs will not include 'index.php'.
In order to support this you must download this file, upload it to your site's directory and rename it to '.htaccess' (with no file name). If there is already a .htaccess file, add the contents of this one to the existing.
If you are not sure how to do this, contact technical support for assistance.

When enabled, Friendly URLs will not include 'index.php'. In order to support this you must configure your web server to rewrite all URLs for your community directory to the index.php file. For assistance on how to do this, contact your hosting provider or system administrator.

AJAX is a technology which allows the content of the page changes dynamically without loading a new page. Invision Community uses this in some areas, particularly when you move between pages. For example, if you are viewing content with more than one page, you will notice that when you move between pages, only part of the page changes, rather than a whole new page is loaded.

Google requires that advertisements be shown immediately when the page loads and not loaded using AJAX. This means that if you place advertisements somewhere that may be loaded with AJAX that you need to disable this feature in Invision Community. To do this:
Go to the Themes section of the AdminCP.
For each Theme that you have installed, click the Edit button.
Disable the 'Use AJAX pagination?' setting and save the Theme.

Google has many other terms which affect how you can use their network and other advertisement networks have similar rules. Make sure you check your network's rules carefully for any additional steps you may need to take.

Routine maintenance tasks need to be performed at regular intervals. View Tasks

The system will automatically run tasks as members browse the site. This is fine for most sites, but if your site does not receive much member traffic, tasks could become backlogged. Tasks will only be triggered by regular members, not guests. If it looks like a backlog is being generated, an error will display on the AdminCP dashboard.
If you are able to set up crons on your web server, the server can run these tasks. This is more reliable and so is recommended if possible on your server.
You can use a web service such as EasyCron to remotely trigger these tasks. This is recommended if your site does not receive much member traffic and using a cron isn't possible.

When this setting is enabled you MUST ensure that the cron is set up properly. If this setting is turned on but no cron is set up it will cause significant damage to your site.

The 'session.gc_maxlifetime' setting in your PHP configuration is set to %s seconds (%s minutes). This setting controls the minimum time a session will be kept after no activity. Having a setting that is too high may mean that sessions are not cleaned correctly which can have performance and security implications, or too low may mean that users are signed out while using the community. We recommend setting this to 1440, which is the default value. Contact your hosting provider or system administrator for assistance changing this setting.

The 'session.gc_probability' setting in your PHP configuration is set to %s, and the 'session.gc_divisor' setting is %s. The first divided by the second (%s with your current configuration) controls the probability that on any page load old sessions will be deleted. Having a probability that is too low may mean that sessions are not cleaned correctly which can have performance and security implications. We recommend setting session.gc_probability to 1 and session.gc_divisor to 100, which are the default values. Contact your hosting provider or system administrator for assistance changing these settings.

Iron March Charter and Mission Statement

Official Iron March Flag

 

Iron March Mission Statement

 

Iron March is a global online fascist community that seeks to become the Forge of the 21st Century Fascist by establishing an online Fascist Space so as to foster and develop internet resources dedicated to the study, understanding and practice of the Fascist Worldview and Lifestyle; and a global Fascist Fraternity in the world for the purpose of creating a non-movement/party form of association between fascists that can in turn lead to the strengthening of existing or formation of new movements that engage in our common struggle worldwide.

Iron March itself is not a movement and never intends to become one, rather it is the platform for the creation of the global Fascist Fraternity and the central communications hub for its members online as well as the HQ for the online Fascist Space and the primary source for studying our worldview, thus acting as the Fascist Alma Mater.

Furthermore, a distinction must be made that Iron March and Iron March forum (i.e. IRONMARCH.ORG) are not synonymous as the intent and ambitions outlined in this Mission Statement clearly show that Iron March has outgrown itself as just an internet forum, now encompassing an array of both online and real world activities and goals, making Iron March a living community while the Iron March forum acts as its online HQ. 

To further explain our intentions each key term mentioned above is explained below:

  • Forge(-ing) of the 21st Century Fascist - the most broad and succinct way of describing our Mission Statement that covers both our online and real world activities, implying that we seeks to create not just mere political and career/hobbyist fascists but rather people who share an inherently different perception of the world and thus live and breathe Fascism 24/7, making it not just a mere ideology but a Worldview and Way of Life or Lifestyle, that in the Modern World would appear as a form of counter-culture.
     
  • Fascist Alma Mater - the role that the Iron March forum plays in educating people towards a more comprehensive understanding of the Fascist Struggle and Worldview, and a common way of referring to any Iron March projects dedicated to further research and education in those fields (ex. Fascist Archive, Antimony Group).
     
  • Fascist Space - common way of referring to all online Iron March projects and online projects/activities created by members of the IM community that in any way further our goals, including educational, creative, demonstrative outlets of the Fascist Lifestyle (ex. NOOSE). The Iron Pride Network is the formal name of this space. 
     
  • Fascist Fraternity - Iron March community manifested in the real world as a means of fascist association that exists outside belonging to any particular movement or party, encouraging fascists to spend time together outside of movement activities or to the contrary bring together fascists with no existing affiliations, to share in common interests or form some organization of their own. It is important to note that in the event of a movement's formation Iron March has no direct control over it and can merely offer advice as a community, in the hopes of nurturing the growth of a successful and dedicated fascist organization.

Most of the planning behind the aforementioned goals and projects occurs on our online HQ - the Iron March forum. As such the Forum Charter in no small part defines the nature of our community and can be used not as only a guide for using the forum itself but also as a point of reference to the standards of our community at large.

Honour Truth - Wage War - Have Fun

 

Official Iron March Crest

 

Iron March Forum Charter
 

I. Adminship

The Adminship are the Iron March Forum Admins, tasked with maintaining the forum, disciplinary actions, enforcing the values of our worldview and the planning of all IM projects to further our common goals.

The official symbol of the Adminship and the Iron March forum is the Machina Hierarchia - Hierarchy Machine (cog and hands) - it symbolizes the organic unity that exists in a proper hierarchy, making it work as smoothly and efficiently as a machine; alternatively it symbolizes the fostering of an organic unity from what were initially mechanical means.

II. Black Corps

The Black Corps are the Iron March Forum Moderators - the most trusted and true who embody both the values that are at the foundation of this community and of the values of our worldview. The Black Corps are tasked with maintaining order and cleanliness on the forum, as well as seeking out and purging unwanted elements as outlined in segment III of this charter (Community). 

To become a member of the Black Corps one must be a long term member of the IM Forum in good standing who has also proven to be responsible and thus worthy of the title and the tasks that come with it.

III. Community

Iron March is not a movement, but we expect users to share our purpose – to take an active interest in using the forum, and when contributing to do so as fascists in ultimate pursuit of knowledge, ideas, contacts, etcetera. Those who are not constructive and threaten this are in the wrong place and unwelcome. We recognize there is a widespread character issue in movement politics, and we start here to address some of those problems here. The following rules are to be observed by all members and handled quickly and diplomatically where possible.

1. No ‘Sperging’. As in ‘Asperger’s syndrome’, an Autistic mental disorder characterized by extreme egocentricity and an inability to understand how to interact socially. This policy is to curtail and recognize the tendencies of users whose actions and motivations are outside our common goals, are deliberately of no benefit to anyone, and only serve to cause trouble. Regardless of whether it is motivated by narcissism, social alienation, cowardice, or stupidity we must control it, and it is the user’s responsibility to observe these following principles which will serve as a guide to ensure there will be no problems for you while you are here.

1.1 - Role-playing. The tendency to portray personal views in the third person with no clear relation to the real world constitutes a form of role-playing. Another form of role-playing is found in arrogance; insisting on special treatment or to be regarded as a separate tier, in contradiction to the fact it is usually marked by an absence of; personal effort, courage, commitment, consistency, positions that will attract negative response, interest in people, etc - by coincidence. If you are a fake you will be recognized and publicly called out.

1.2 - Fashion Fascism. Fascism isn't a fetish – if you regularly treat it as such your motivations will be questioned as ulterior. If you reflect your political ‘identity’ in things like science fiction or anything else found in Television, Video games, hobbies, sub-cultures etc, it tells us that you are unable to distinguish between the two.

1.3 - Shitposting. Making shit posts; this happens when a post is devoid of content or context, eg randomly responding with a reaction image. If you have nothing else to contribute you have no right to be engaging in this.

1.4 - Constructive debate. The goal of debate is the pursuit of truth therefore you should take care about what you are saying and care about opposing arguments and should assume it is the same for your opponent – so where relevant you should be capable of providing sources to back up an opinion - this is an argument. Ignoring responses while continuing to argue shows you have no investment in the discussion and also, that you have nothing to offer or contribute.

1.5 - Conduct. It is your responsibility to judge group relations and know what not to post and where things should be posted. When you can participate in a forum drama, promote yourself, become insolent towards members, etc, is something only you can judge.

If these are not monitored by the user and kept in check it may result in messages of warning from moderators.

2. This is not Stormfront. Our community is based on discussion and debate constructive towards fascist goals, it is not a hangout for White Nationalists and their unique subculture. Stormfront and VNN forums already provide this in terms of its endless topics on conspiracy theories, chimpouts, Zionism, etcetera. Exclusively posting remarks and threads of that nature without proper context is a form of spamming.

Likewise, we are not a New Right intellectual circle jerk and we do not tolerate aimless, abstract philosophizing and the typical self-important snobbish behavior that comes with it. Furthermore we recognize displays of such behavior to be a form of violation of points outlined in segment III of this charter (Community).

3. Tolerance. We accept people with strong viewpoints even if ultimately we seek everyone to join us in our comprehension of the world, whilst also understanding that this can be accomplished only so far via our internet forum platform. Those who take themselves too seriously yet refuse to debate become paranoid, patronizing, passive aggressive and can become the source of drama. Users of non straight-white-male-fascist backgrounds also need to be conscious of their differences and check their privilege at the door. If you have allowed yourself to become aggravated through your own fault we will not side with you and you may be held responsible.

4. Sophian Language. You are expected to use this website with intelligence, knowing what not to write and to read between the lines. By posting here you need to personally be prepared it might be read in a court, quoted on in a newspaper, or read to your weeping mother – and hold yourself to account. Don't ask us to delete all your posts because you have "changed your mind.", or even attempt to alter them yourself. Remember, your public posts are cached by search engines or may be recorded by others.

5. Untermenschen. Just being you can result in an immediate ban, and we will take immediate and permanent action if it is ever found out the following applies to you.

5.1 - We do not allow or entertain the mentally ill to the extent they cannot understand fascism, (for instance those who do genuinely suffer from Autism) and it is our responsibility to direct them away from this place because they should not be here.

5.2 - Expression of interest in Paedophilia (Including any similar inclinations towards the under-aged) will result immediate ban, and even the slightest hint will be treated seriously.

5.3 - Simply put, we reserve the right to ban you if you are any kind of faggot. If you feel the need to tell the world then you will bring the consequences on yourself just as hard. Belonging to the furry fandom is prohibited, partly because it also involves a breach of 1.1 and 1.2, but mostly because it is utterly degenerative (it deserves note here because it will apply even if explicitly sexual grounds cannot be ascertained).

Failure to comply may result in internment, when a member's activity on the forum is restricted to the Showers. These members will be marked as Prisoners and they will inevitably be Gassed.

IV. Forum Activities

Iron March Forum provides it's users with a number of activities that help us develop as a forum, an information center and a community for fellow fascists as well as establish new projects outside the Forum both online and in real life. Any user can officially sign up for any such activity and become an active contributor. Simply follow the rules of each such activity and you will find yourself occupied with interesting projects that will help you develop your skills or further your knowledge.

V. Discipline

We expect every user to follow the rules set forth by the Adminship.

1. Our community is interested in active members, not lurkers and defunct profiles. All accounts that have zero posts for a week after registry on the forum will be deleted. At least once a year (sometime in January) the forum undergoes a purge of defunct profiles, meaning profiles that have been inactive for a period of one year will be are permanently deleted. Profiles with large post counts will be spared, however the minimum post count required to avoid account deletion increases over time. 

2. Before creating a new topic make sure that a similar one doesn't already exist and be sure to post topics in the appropriate sections of the Iron March forum. Use the search bar in the top right corner if  you are not sure where to look.

3. Do not derail topics, do not flame, do not spam.

*It is the user’s responsibility not to be trolled.

4. Follow the respective rules of all forum activities and projects as they are explained in the sections dedicated to those activities.

5. Moderators and Admins may dispense punishment at their discretion and can give formal warnings to users who behave in an unacceptable manner (unnecessary aggression, blatant and systematic disregard of the forum rules and etc). Punishments vary from preliminary warnings and temporary suspension to immediate gassings with no warning at all. 

VI. Uniform

1. Forum avatars are restricted to a size of 160x160 pixels, and 50 kb.

2. Forum signatures are restricted to one image of 800x140 pixels and 5 lines of text.

3. Admins can be recognized by the symbol of the Iron March Adminship below their title and avatar - Machina Hierarchia and Admins Wreath.

4. Members of the Black Corps can be recognized by the symbol of the Black Corps below their title and avatar - the Sword and Shield, combined with the Machina Hierarchia. Black Corps Captain is recognized by the same symbol with wings.

5. Users are discouraged from taking the names of historic persons, eg ‘Benito Mussolini’, and may be asked to change their username.
 

Follow these rules diligently, least you face the wrath of the Adminship.

Gas the Kikes, Race War Now! 1488 Boots on the Ground!

  • Fascist Space - common way of referring to all online Iron March projects and online projects/activities created by members of the IM community that in any way further our goals, including educational, creative, demonstrative outlets of the Fascist Lifestyle (ex. NOOSE). The Iron Pride Network is the formal name of this space. 
     
  • Fascist Fraternity - Iron March community manifested in the real world as a means of fascist association that exists outside belonging to any particular movement or party, encouraging fascists to spend time together outside of movement activities or to the contrary bring together fascists with no existing affiliations, to share in common interests or form some organization of their own. It is important to note that in the event of a movement's formation Iron March has no direct control over it and can merely offer advice as a community, in the hopes of nurturing the growth of a successful and dedicated fascist organization.

Most of the planning behind the aforementioned goals and projects occurs on our online HQ - the Iron March forum. As such the Forum Charter in no small part defines the nature of our community and can be used not as only a guide for using the forum itself but also as a point of reference to the standards of our community at large.

Honour Truth - Wage War - Have Fun

 

Official Iron March Crest

 

Iron March Forum Charter
 

I. Adminship

The Adminship are the Iron March Forum Admins, tasked with maintaining the forum, disciplinary actions, enforcing the values of our worldview and the planning of all IM projects to further our common goals.

The official symbol of the Adminship and the Iron March forum is the Machina Hierarchia - Hierarchy Machine (cog and hands) - it symbolizes the organic unity that exists in a proper hierarchy, making it work as smoothly and efficiently as a machine; alternatively it symbolizes the fostering of an organic unity from what were initially mechanical means.

II. Black Corps

The Black Corps are the Iron March Forum Moderators - the most trusted and true who embody both the values that are at the foundation of this community and of the values of our worldview. The Black Corps are tasked with maintaining order and cleanliness on the forum, as well as seeking out and purging unwanted elements as outlined in segment III of this charter (Community). 

To become a member of the Black Corps one must be a long term member of the IM Forum in good standing who has also proven to be responsible and thus worthy of the title and the tasks that come with it.

III. Community

Iron March is not a movement, but we expect users to share our purpose – to take an active interest in using the forum, and when contributing to do so as fascists in ultimate pursuit of knowledge, ideas, contacts, etcetera. Those who are not constructive and threaten this are in the wrong place and unwelcome. We recognize there is a widespread character issue in movement politics, and we start here to address some of those problems here. The following rules are to be observed by all members and handled quickly and diplomatically where possible.

1. No ‘Sperging’. As in ‘Asperger’s syndrome’, an Autistic mental disorder characterized by extreme egocentricity and an inability to understand how to interact socially. This policy is to curtail and recognize the tendencies of users whose actions and motivations are outside our common goals, are deliberately of no benefit to anyone, and only serve to cause trouble. Regardless of whether it is motivated by narcissism, social alienation, cowardice, or stupidity we must control it, and it is the user’s responsibility to observe these following principles which will serve as a guide to ensure there will be no problems for you while you are here.

1.1 - Role-playing. The tendency to portray personal views in the third person with no clear relation to the real world constitutes a form of role-playing. Another form of role-playing is found in arrogance; insisting on special treatment or to be regarded as a separate tier, in contradiction to the fact it is usually marked by an absence of; personal effort, courage, commitment, consistency, positions that will attract negative response, interest in people, etc - by coincidence. If you are a fake you will be recognized and publicly called out.

1.2 - Fashion Fascism. Fascism isn't a fetish – if you regularly treat it as such your motivations will be questioned as ulterior. If you reflect your political ‘identity’ in things like science fiction or anything else found in Television, Video games, hobbies, sub-cultures etc, it tells us that you are unable to distinguish between the two.

1.3 - Shitposting. Making shit posts; this happens when a post is devoid of content or context, eg randomly responding with a reaction image. If you have nothing else to contribute you have no right to be engaging in this.

1.4 - Constructive debate. The goal of debate is the pursuit of truth therefore you should take care about what you are saying and care about opposing arguments and should assume it is the same for your opponent – so where relevant you should be capable of providing sources to back up an opinion - this is an argument. Ignoring responses while continuing to argue shows you have no investment in the discussion and also, that you have nothing to offer or contribute.

1.5 - Conduct. It is your responsibility to judge group relations and know what not to post and where things should be posted. When you can participate in a forum drama, promote yourself, become insolent towards members, etc, is something only you can judge.

If these are not monitored by the user and kept in check it may result in messages of warning from moderators.

2. This is not Stormfront. Our community is based on discussion and debate constructive towards fascist goals, it is not a hangout for White Nationalists and their unique subculture. Stormfront and VNN forums already provide this in terms of its endless topics on conspiracy theories, chimpouts, Zionism, etcetera. Exclusively posting remarks and threads of that nature without proper context is a form of spamming.

Likewise, we are not a New Right intellectual circle jerk and we do not tolerate aimless, abstract philosophizing and the typical self-important snobbish behavior that comes with it. Furthermore we recognize displays of such behavior to be a form of violation of points outlined in segment III of this charter (Community).

3. Tolerance. We accept people with strong viewpoints even if ultimately we seek everyone to join us in our comprehension of the world, whilst also understanding that this can be accomplished only so far via our internet forum platform. Those who take themselves too seriously yet refuse to debate become paranoid, patronizing, passive aggressive and can become the source of drama. Users of non straight-white-male-fascist backgrounds also need to be conscious of their differences and check their privilege at the door. If you have allowed yourself to become aggravated through your own fault we will not side with you and you may be held responsible.

4. Sophian Language. You are expected to use this website with intelligence, knowing what not to write and to read between the lines. By posting here you need to personally be prepared it might be read in a court, quoted on in a newspaper, or read to your weeping mother – and hold yourself to account. Don't ask us to delete all your posts because you have "changed your mind.", or even attempt to alter them yourself. Remember, your public posts are cached by search engines or may be recorded by others.

5. Untermenschen. Just being you can result in an immediate ban, and we will take immediate and permanent action if it is ever found out the following applies to you.

5.1 - We do not allow or entertain the mentally ill to the extent they cannot understand fascism, (for instance those who do genuinely suffer from Autism) and it is our responsibility to direct them away from this place because they should not be here.

5.2 - Expression of interest in Paedophilia (Including any similar inclinations towards the under-aged) will result immediate ban, and even the slightest hint will be treated seriously.

5.3 - Simply put, we reserve the right to ban you if you are any kind of faggot. If you feel the need to tell the world then you will bring the consequences on yourself just as hard. Belonging to the furry fandom is prohibited, partly because it also involves a breach of 1.1 and 1.2, but mostly because it is utterly degenerative (it deserves note here because it will apply even if explicitly sexual grounds cannot be ascertained).

Failure to comply may result in internment, when a member's activity on the forum is restricted to the Showers. These members will be marked as Prisoners and they will inevitably be Gassed.

IV. Forum Activities

Iron March Forum provides it's users with a number of activities that help us develop as a forum, an information center and a community for fellow fascists as well as establish new projects outside the Forum both online and in real life. Any user can officially sign up for any such activity and become an active contributor. Simply follow the rules of each such activity and you will find yourself occupied with interesting projects that will help you develop your skills or further your knowledge.

V. Discipline

We expect every user to follow the rules set forth by the Adminship.

1. Our community is interested in active members, not lurkers and defunct profiles. All accounts that have zero posts for a week after registry on the forum will be deleted. At least once a year (sometime in January) the forum undergoes a purge of defunct profiles, meaning profiles that have been inactive for a period of one year will be are permanently deleted. Profiles with large post counts will be spared, however the minimum post count required to avoid account deletion increases over time. 

2. Before creating a new topic make sure that a similar one doesn't already exist and be sure to post topics in the appropriate sections of the Iron March forum. Use the search bar in the top right corner if  you are not sure where to look.

3. Do not derail topics, do not flame, do not spam.

*It is the user’s responsibility not to be trolled.

4. Follow the respective rules of all forum activities and projects as they are explained in the sections dedicated to those activities.

5. Moderators and Admins may dispense punishment at their discretion and can give formal warnings to users who behave in an unacceptable manner (unnecessary aggression, blatant and systematic disregard of the forum rules and etc). Punishments vary from preliminary warnings and temporary suspension to immediate gassings with no warning at all. 

VI. Uniform

1. Forum avatars are restricted to a size of 160x160 pixels, and 50 kb.

2. Forum signatures are restricted to one image of 800x140 pixels and 5 lines of text.

3. Admins can be recognized by the symbol of the Iron March Adminship below their title and avatar - Machina Hierarchia and Admins Wreath.

4. Members of the Black Corps can be recognized by the symbol of the Black Corps below their title and avatar - the Sword and Shield, combined with the Machina Hierarchia. Black Corps Captain is recognized by the same symbol with wings.

5. Users are discouraged from taking the names of historic persons, eg ‘Benito Mussolini’, and may be asked to change their username.
 

Follow these rules diligently, least you face the wrath of the Adminship.

Gas the Kikes, Race War Now! 1488 Boots on the Ground!

If you have a very large site, it can be beneficial to reduce the size of the database table storing posts. Archiving topics is an alternative to deleting which allows them to still exist and be viewed as normal, but moves them to a separate database table. Archived topics cannot be posted in or edited, and will not show in search results. You can unarchive topics after they've been archived if you change your mind.
word_custom: Если у вас очень большой сайт, это может быть выгодно для уменьшения размера таблицы базы данных, в которой хранятся сообщения. Архивирование тем является альтернативой удалению, но они по-прежнему доступны. Основное отличие в том, что они перемещаются в отдельную таблицу в базе данных и недоступны для изменения. Вы сможете восстановить темы из архива в любое время.

word_default: The 'session.gc_probability' setting in your PHP configuration is set to %s, and the 'session.gc_divisor' setting is %s. The first divided by the second (%s with your current configuration) controls the probability that on any page load old sessions will be deleted. Having a probability that is too low may mean that sessions are not cleaned correctly which can have performance and security implications. We recommend setting session.gc_probability to 1 and session.gc_divisor to 100, which are the default values. Contact your hosting provider or system administrator for assistance changing these settings.
word_custom: Параметр 'session.gc_probability' вашей конфигурации PHP имеет значение %s и 'session.gc_divisor' имеет значение %s. Первый параметр делится на секунды (%s в вашей текущей конфигурации) и контролирует вероятность удаления старых сессий при загрузке страницы. Если установлено слишком низкое значение, сессии не будут очищаться корректно, что может вызвать проблемы с производительностью и безопасностью. Рекомендуется установить значение session.gc_probability равным 1, и  session.gc_divisor равным 100, что является стандартным. Свяжитесь с технической поддержкой или системным администратором для помощи в изменении этого значения.

word_default: The 'session.gc_maxlifetime' setting in your PHP configuration is set to %s seconds (%s minutes). This setting controls the minimum time a session will be kept after no activity. Having a setting that is too high may mean that sessions are not cleaned correctly which can have performance and security implications, or too low may mean that users are signed out while using the community. We recommend setting this to 1440, which is the default value. Contact your hosting provider or system administrator for assistance changing this setting.
word_custom: Параметр 'session.gc_maxlifetime' вашей конфигурации PHP имеет значение %s секунд (%s минут). Этот параметр контролирует минимальное время хранения сессии после отсутствия активности. Если установлено слишком высокое значение, сессии не будут очищаться корректно, что может вызвать проблемы с производительностью и безопасностью. А слишком низкое значение может вызвать принудительный выход пользователей в момент посещения ими сайта. Рекомендуется установить это значение равным 1440, что является стандартным. Свяжитесь с технической поддержкой или системным администратором для помощи в изменении этого значения.

word_default: It is important to protect your site from a user uploading a malicious file and using it to compromise your server. To do this, a .htaccess file can be written to the directories where files are uploaded to instruct the server to always treat them as attachments and never execute them.

После выполнения данной рекомендации, в потенциально опасные директории будет записан файл .htaccess, который позволит запретить выполнять вредоносные файлы.

word_default: If your site is likely to be used by many users in an intranet situation (such as an office or university), you may need to disable this setting to prevent users being logged out. However, when disabled, there is a greater risk of session hijacking. In most environments, this setting should be left on.
word_custom: Если ваш сайт работает в интранете (например, в офисе или университете), вам, возможно, потребуется отключить этот параметр, чтобы запретить пользователям выход из системы. Однако, при отключении злоумышленник может произвести подмену сессии. На большинстве сайтов этот параметр должен быть включен.

word_default: Check IP address when validating session?

If your network environment means requests are handled through a proxy (such as in an intranet situation in an office or university, or on a load-balanced server cluster), you may need to enable this setting so that the correct IP address is used. However, when enabled, a malicious user can abuse the system to provide a fake IP address. In most environments, this setting should be left off.
word_custom: Если провайдер обрабатывает ваши запросы через прокси-сервер (например, в интранете), вам, возможно, потребуется включить этот параметр, чтобы мы корректно проверяли используемые IP-адреса. Однако, при включении злоумышленник может произвести подмену IP-адресов. На большинстве сайтов этот параметр должен быть выключен.

word_default: Trust IP addresses provided by proxies?

Routine maintenance tasks are performed as users access the site but it looks like the traffic to your community is not sufficient to run these tasks on time. It is recommended that you set up a cron or a web service to ensure a backlog is not created. Мы рекомендуем вам настроить cron или веб-сервис, чтобы убедиться, что задачи не откладываются. word_default: There are some issues communicating with {# [1:site][?:sites]} in your IPS Connect network. Until the site or sites can be reached, some account changes may not show on those sites.
word_custom: Возникли проблемы со связью с {# [0:сайтами][1:сайтом][*1:сайтом][?:сайтами]} в вашей сети IPS Connect. До тех пор, пока сайт или сайты не будут исправлены, некоторые изменения аккаунта могут не отображаться на этих сайтах.

word_default: By removing a site from the network, account changes will no longer be copied to that site. You should only do this if the site no longer exists or IPS Connect has been disabled on it.
word_custom: После отключения сайта от сети, изменения в аккаунтах больше не будут копироваться на этот сайт. Вы должны делать это, только если сайт более не существует или он был отключён от IPS Connect.

word_default: There are no failed requests queued
word_custom: Нет неудачных запросов к IPS Connect

word_default: There are no users awaiting approval
There are no failed administrator logins
There was a problem fetching the latest news
word_custom: Возникла проблема с получением последних новостей

word_default: As there are no translated language keys, there is nothing to download.
word_custom: Загрузка невозможна т.к. отсутствуют переведённые строки

word_default: Translated language phrase with key '%s' in language '%s'
word_custom: Переведена фраза с ключом "%s" в языке "%s"

word_default:
When enabled, rather than viewing the real words and phrases, the keys that represent them will show. This can be useful for seeing what key a particular word or phrase is stored as. This will only affect your account.
If you are unable to find this setting again after enabling it, exit and then reopen your web browser to disable.
word_custom: Эта функция позволяет включить отображения ключей языковых строк вместо их содержимого. Полезно, если вы хотите узнать какая языковая строка отвечает за какое-либо слово или фразу. Данная возможность будет активирована только для вашего аккаунта.Если вы не можете найти эту настройку после её включения, выйдите с сайта и зайдите снова.

word_default: The quick translating tool cannot be used while development mode is enabled.
word_custom: Визуальный перевод не может быть включен, пока включен режим разработки.

word_default: When enabled, you can click and hold on any word or phrase on your site to quickly translate it for the language you are viewing the site in. This will only affect your account.
word_custom: Эта функция позволяет переводить слова и фразы после нажатия и удержания левой кнопки мыши над ними. Данная возможность будет активирована только для вашего аккаунта.

word_default: Members who are using the language you are disabling will be moved to the selected language instead.
word_custom: Пользователи, которые используют отключаемый язык, станут использовать указанный язык.

word_default: Use if a member has not specifically set a language and it cannot be determined automatically from their browser.
word_custom: Используется, если пользователь не выбрал нужный язык вручную и он не может быть автоматически определён, согласно настройкам браузера.

word_default: The chosen locale is not supported by your server. Your hosting provider or system administrator will be able to provide a list of the locales supported by your server.
word_custom: Выбранная локаль не поддерживается сервером. Ваш хостинг-провайдер или системный администратор могут предоставить вам список локалей, поддерживаемых сервером.

word_default: For Western languages, this is left-to-right
word_custom: Направление текста зависит от языка. Для русского языка это слева направо

word_default: Your hosting provider or system administrator will be able to provide a list of the locales supported by your server.
word_custom: Ваш хостинг-провайдер или системный администратор могут предоставить вам список локалей, поддерживаемых сервером.

word_default: Upload the new constants.php file before clicking continue.
To save your configuration, you must download a new constants.php file and upload it to the root directory of your site.
word_custom: Для сохранения настроек вы должны скачать файл constants.php и загрузить его в корневую директорию вашего сайта.

word_default: The servers provided are not valid.
You must provide at least one server.
word_custom: Вы должны предоставить как минимум один сервер.

word_default: The directory must exist and be writable.
word_custom: Директория должна существовать и быть доступна для записи.

word_default: You must provide a server hostname and either leave the server port blank, or supply a valid port number
word_custom: Вы должны указать адрес сервера и при необходимости указать номер порта.

word_default: In order to use this method, the %s extension must be installed on your server.
word_custom: Для использования этого метода на сервере также должен быть установлен %s.

word_default: The caching method is used by various systems for temporary data storage and data caching. All options apart from Memcached use server memory and using any of these will increase performance over not caching. Memcached is a distributed memory object caching system and provides the best performance.
word_custom: Кэширование используется различными системами для временного хранения кэшированных данных. Все варианты, кроме Memcached, используют память сервера и использование любого из них окажет прирост производительности по сравнению с отсутствием кэширования. Memcached является распределенной системой кэширования в памяти, что обеспечивает лучшую производительность.

word_default: The data storage method is used by various systems to save arbitrary data. If caching is enabled, using the MySQL Database provides the best performance for most environments, otherwise using the File System is usually best.
word_custom: Метод хранения данных используются системой и приложениями. Если кэширование включено, использование базы данных MySQL обеспечивает наилучшую производительность для большинства сред. В противном случае лучшим выбором будет файловая система.

word_default: You cannot manage friendly URLs while in developer mode unless you set the constant \IPS\DEV_USE_FURL_CACHE to true.
word_custom: Вы не можете использовать ЧПУ в режиме разработчика, пока не измените значение константы \IPS\DEV_USE_FURL_CACHE на true.

word_default: You do not need to include any parameters which are specified as variables in the Friendly URL.
word_custom: Вам не нужно включать любые параметры, которые указаны в качестве переменных, в ЧПУ.

word_default:
Encase variables in {curly braces} containing either a # (for numbers) or @ (for text) symbol, followed by the name of the parameter that matches in the real URL. e.g. {#showtopic} will match the 'showtopic' parameter in the real URL.
{?} marks the position of variables that do not appear in the real URL such as topic titles.
word_custom:
Заключите переменные в {фигурные скобки}, содержащие символ # (для чисел) или @ (для текста), затем название параметра, который будет отображаться в ссылке. Например, {#showtopic} соответствует параметру "showtopic" в реальном адресе.
{?} отмечайте местоположение переменных, которые не должны быть указаны в ссылке. Например, название темы.

word_default: Adjusting these settings is recommended only for advanced users. Custom URLs are not backwards compatible with the default URLs and so any changes will have an immediate negative effect on your search engine rankings.
word_custom: Изменять эти настройки рекомендуется только продвинутым пользователям. Пользовательские ссылки не являются обратно совместимыми с ссылками по умолчанию и поэтому любые изменения будут отрицательно влиять на ваш рейтинг в поисковых системах.

word_default: Prunes validating members older than 30 days.
word_custom: Удаляет пользователей, ожидающих проверки более 30 дней.

word_default: Tasks do not usually log anything if they run without error.
word_custom: Задачи обычно не журналируются, если они завершились без ошибок.

word_default: The task ran successfully and produced the following output:
word_custom: Задача успешно запущена и был получен следующий результат:

word_default: The task is already running and cannot be ran until it has finished or the lock is removed.
word_custom: Задача уже выполняется и не может быть запущена, пока она не остановится или блокировка не снимется.

word_default: Sends out daily and weekly digest emails for followed content.
word_custom: Отправляет ежедневные и еженедельные дайджесты публикаций.

word_default: Can't log in to POP3 mail server
word_custom: Невозможно авторизоваться на POP3 сервере почты

word_default: Can't connect to POP3 mail server
word_custom: Невозможно подключиться к POP3 серверу почты

word_default: Fetches and parses incoming POP3 emails.
word_custom: Забирает и анализирует входящую электронную почту через POP3.

word_default: Reattempts any failed IPS Connect requests.
word_custom: Повторяет все неудавшиеся запросы к IPS Connect.

word_default: Deletes old temporary data, prunes logs, deleted moved-content links and removes expired warning points.
word_custom: Удаляет старые временные данные, очищает журналы, удаляет ссылки на перемещённое содержимое и удаляет истёкшие баллы предупреждений.

word_default: Updates the sitemap with the latest content from the community and submits to search engines.
word_custom: Обновляет карту сайта с последними публикациями сайта и предоставляет её поисковым системам.

word_default: Sends any bulk emails waiting to be sent.
Checks for updates to applications, plugins and themes.
word_custom: Проверяет наличие обновлений для приложений, плагинов и стилей.

word_default: Syncs profile data from external services.
word_custom: Синхронизирует данные профилей со сторонних сервисов.

word_default: In order to enable this setting you must make the %s file executable (i.e. chmod 0777).
word_custom: Для того чтобы включить эту настройку, необходимо сделать файл %s исполняемым (т.е. chmod 0777).

word_default:
When this setting is enabled you MUST ensure that a web service calls to the following URL. If this setting is turned on but no web service is set up it will cause significant damage to your site.

You should set the service to call to the following URL as frequently as every minute (or as frequently as possible):
%s
word_custom:
Если эта настройка включена, вы ДОЛЖНЫ убедиться в том, что веб-сервис обращается к указанной ссылке. Если эта настройка включена, но веб-сервис не настроен, это может вызвать повреждение вашего сайта.

Вы должны настроить веб-сервис на обращение по указанной ссылке каждую минуту (или как можно чаще):
%s

word_default:
When this setting is enabled you MUST ensure that the cron is set up properly. If this setting is turned on but no cron is set up it will cause significant damage to your site.

You should set the cron to run the following command every minute:
%s
word_custom:
Если эта настройка включена, вы ДОЛЖНЫ убедиться в том, что cron настроен корректно. Если эта настройка включена, но cron не настроен, это может вызвать повреждение вашего сайта.

Вы должны настроить cron на запуск этой команды каждую минуту:
%s

word_default: You can use a web service such as EasyCron to remotely trigger these tasks. This is recommended if your site does not receive much member traffic and using a cron isn't possible.
word_custom: Вы можете использовать веб-сервис, такой как EasyCron, для удалённого запуска этих задач. Подходит для сайтов с недостаточным трафиком пользователей и при невозможности использования Cron.

word_default: If you are able to set up crons on your web server, the server can run these tasks. This is more reliable and so is recommended if possible on your server.
word_custom: Если у вас есть возможность настроить Cron на вашем сервере, он может выполнять эти задачи самостоятельно. Это более надёжно и рекомендуется использовать этот метод, если он возможен на вашем сервере.

word_default: The system will automatically run tasks as members browse the site. This is fine for most sites, but if your site does not receive much member traffic, tasks could become backlogged. Tasks will only be triggered by regular members, not guests. If it looks like a backlog is being generated, an error will display on the AdminCP dashboard.
word_custom: Система будет автоматически запускать задачи, когда пользователи просматривают сайт. Подходит для большинства сайтов, но если пользователи вашего сайта не обеспечивают достаточный трафик, то задачи будут откладываться. Задачи будут выполняться только при посещении пользователями, не гостями. Если задачи будут отлажены, отобразится специальное сообщение на Главной панели Админцентра.

word_default: Routine maintenance tasks need to be performed at regular intervals. View Tasks
word_custom: Плановые работы по техническому обслуживанию выполняются при посещении сайта пользователями. При создании Cron сервер сможет выполнять эти задачи самостоятельно. Просмотреть задачи

word_default: Invision Community will make automatic AJAX requests to your server to facilitate instant notifications, showing when a user has replied to content and other features. These requests are made in an efficient manner and the rate slows with the amount of time a user is inactive, but you may want to disable these features if you need to reduce the amount of requests to your server.
word_custom: IPS Community Suite будет автоматически отправлять AJAX-запросы на ваш сервер для улучшения мгновенных уведомлений, отображаемых пользователям, когда кто-либо ответил на публикацию и в других случаях. Эти запросы сделаны эффективным способом так, что их количество уменьшается в течении всего времени неактивности пользователя, но вы можете отключить их, если вам нужно уменьшить количество запросов к серверу.

word_default: Note: changing this setting will not recalculate current votes. This will mean that any current votes will be calculated at either half or double their true value.
word_custom: Примечание: изменение этой настройки не изменит текущий рейтинг. Это значит, что рейтинг может стать в два раза больше или в два раза меньше.

word_default: Some content when being moved will leave a link in the old location pointing to the new. This setting allows you to automatically remove the links.
word_custom: Некоторые материалы при перемещении могут оставлять ссылку со старого расположения на новое. Этот параметр позволяет автоматически удалять данные ссылки.

word_default: New posts within a short time frame are limited. Please wait %s seconds before submitting.
word_custom: Установлен лимит на отправку нескольких сообщений за определённое время. Пожалуйста, подождите %s секунд перед отправкой.

word_default: After a user has made a post or comment, they cannot make any additional posts for the specified length of time, unless the above setting for merging concurrent posts applies. You can disable this for individual groups in the group settings.
word_custom: После того, как пользователь отправит сообщение и комментарий, он не сможет отправить другое сообщение в течение определённого времени, если настройка слияния параллельных сообщений выше включена. Вы можете отключить это для определённых групп в настройках групп.

word_default: If a user makes a post or comment, and then makes another post or comment on the same item within the specified timeframe before any other user, the posts will be merged. This bypasses any limit the user has on editing their posts.
word_custom: Если пользователь отправляет комментарий и затем снова отправляет комментарий к той же публикации в определённый промежуток времени до любого другого пользователя, то его комментарии будут объединены. Запрет на редактирование сообщений не влияет на эту функцию.

word_default: Logged content edits older than the period specified will be pruned
word_custom: Записи в журнале изменений будет очищены через указанный период.

word_default:
When disabled, only moderators who have permission to view the edit log can see what was changed (other users can just see when the content was last edited).
When enabled, all users will be able to see the details of changes the author has made to the content. Edits made by moderators are still only shown to moderators.
word_custom:
При отключении, только модераторы смогут просматривать журнал изменений публикаций. Остальные пользователи будут видеть только дату последнего изменения.
При включении, все пользователи смогут видеть историю изменений содержимого. Изменения, внесённые модератором, отображаться не будут.

word_default: Log that an edit has been made and show when content was last edited
word_custom: Сохранять список изменений и дату последнего

word_default: Log all edits made to content and what was changed
word_custom: Сохранять всё содержимое и его изменения

word_default: Show full log to all users?

This setting restricts the size of content (such as videos) from embedded links. The content will never be wider than the user's browser can display, and changing this setting won't apply to existing content.
word_custom: Эта настройка ограничивает размер встраиваемого видео. Видео никогда не будет шире, чем может отобразить браузер пользователя и этот параметр не будет применяться для уже существующих публикаций.

word_default:
Certain content can be automatically embedded. For example, if a user posts a link to a video on YouTube or Vimeo the video can be embedded into the post. Changing this setting won't apply to existing content.
Links from the following sites are supported: College Humor, Facebook, Flickr, Gfycat, Google+, Hulu, Instagram, SoundCloud, Spotify, Ted, Twitter, Vimeo, Vine, YouTube, and internal links to content within the community.
word_custom:
Некоторый контент может быть автоматически встроен. Например, если пользователь отправляет ссылку на видео с YouTube или с Vimeo, то видео будет встроено в сообщение. Изменение этой настройки не затронет уже существующие публикации.
Поддерживаются следующие сайты: College Humor, Facebook, Flickr, Gfycat, Google+, Hulu, Instagram, SoundCloud, Spotify, Ted, Twitter, Vimeo, Vine, YouTube, а так же внутренние ссылки на публикации внутри сообщества.

word_default: The attachment thumbnails will be rebuilt in the background
word_custom: Миниатюры вложений будут перестроены в фоновом режиме

word_default: If an image larger than the these dimensions is uploaded, a thumbnail will be created no bigger than the specified dimensions which is what will be displayed. When the user clicks on this thumbnail, the full-sized image is displayed. It is usually best to keep this quite large so images appear attractive unless your community uses a lot of images and you want to reduce bandwidth use. The settings apply to new images only, unless you rebuild existing images.
word_custom: Если загруженное изображение больше указанного размера, то размер созданной и отображаемой миниатюры будет не больше указанных размеров. При нажатии на неё, изображение откроется в полном размере. Обычно лучше указывать довольно большой максимальный размер до тех пор, пока ваше сообщество не начнёт хранить большое количество изображений и вы захотите уменьшить трафик. Эта настройка влияет только на новые изображения до тех пор, пока вы не перестроите существующие изображения.

word_default: If an image larger than the these dimensions is uploaded, it will be resized to no bigger than the dimensions and the original image will be discarded. Resizing images reduces their quality so it is normally best to leave this unlimited unless your community uses a lot of images and you want to reduce disk space use.
word_custom: Если загруженное изображение больше указанного размера, то его размер будет уменьшен до указанных размеров. Изменение размеров изображений приводит к ухудшению их качества, поэтому рекомендуется не ограничивать это значение, если ваш сайт не хранит большое количество изображений и дисковое пространство не является для вас проблемой.

word_default: If provided, only files which have a name ending in one of the specified extensions will be allowed.
word_custom: Если указано, будут разрешены только те файлы, которые заканчиваются указанными расширениями.

word_default: You can configure which groups can use attachments and their storage limits in the group settings.
word_custom: Вы можете настроить какие группы могут прикреплять файлы к публикациям и их лимиты в настройках групп.

word_default: rel='nofollow' will not be added to any links to the domains specified. Add any domains which your site is connected to or has control over.
word_custom: rel='nofollow' не будет добавляться к ссылкам на доменные имена, которые указаны здесь. Добавьте любые домены, с которыми связан ваш сайт или контролирует.

word_default: Domains to instruct search engines to follow
word_custom: Домены, на которые должны переходить поисковые системы.

word_default: Instruct search engines not to follow posted links?
Will add rel='nofollow' to posted links that link away from your website. This is recommended so search engines are aware that your site is not connected to sites users post links to.
word_custom: Добавить rel='nofollow' к публикуемым внешним ссылкам. Рекомендуется сделать это, чтобы поисковые системы не связывали ваш сайт с сайтами, ссылки на которые публикуют пользователи.

word_default: Setting this to Yes will force all posted links, to other websites, to open in a new window.
word_custom: Если включено, все публикуемые внешние ссылки будут открываться в новой вкладке.

word_default: Force posted links to open in new windows?

word_custom: Используйте * в качестве символа подстановки, например, "http://*.example.com/*"
Используйте * в качестве символа подстановки, например, "http://*.example.com/*"

word_default: Allow any links apart from the links specified
If a user has signed in with Twitter they will see a checkbox when submitting content to share it on Twitter after posting.
word_custom: Если пользователь привязан аккаунт Twitter, то при отправке публикации он увидит флажок, который позволит поделиться ею в Twitter.

word_default: To enable this option, you need to set up Twitter login.
word_custom: Для включения этой настройки вам нужно настроить вход через Twitter.

word_default: Users can share immediately when posting?
word_custom: Пользователи могут поделиться контентом при его публикации

word_default: To enable this option, you need to set up Facebook login.
word_custom: Для включения этой настройки вам нужно настроить вход через Facebook.

word_default:
If a user has signed in with Facebook they will see a checkbox when submitting content to share it on Facebook after posting.

Google requires that advertisements be shown immediately when the page loads and not loaded using AJAX. This means that if you place advertisements somewhere that may be loaded with AJAX that you need to disable this feature in Invision Community. To do this:
word_custom: Google требует немедленно отображение рекламы после загрузки страницы и запрещает их загрузку через AJAX. Это означает, что если вы разместите рекламу там, где доступна загрузка через AJAX, то вам необходимо будет отключить эту возможность в IPS Community Suite. Чтобы сделать это:

word_default: AJAX is a technology which allows the content of the page changes dynamically without loading a new page. Invision Community uses this in some areas, particularly when you move between pages. For example, if you are viewing content with more than one page, you will notice that when you move between pages, only part of the page changes, rather than a whole new page is loaded.
word_custom: AJAX является технологией, позволяющей динамически загружать содержимое страницы без перезагрузки страницы. IPS Community Suite использует её в некоторых областях сайта. Например, при просмотре тем с более одной страницей, вы можете заметить, что при перемещении по страницам загружается только часть страницы и страница не перезагружается полностью.

Если это не так, то убедитесь, что вы правильно загрузили файл .htaccess или обратитесь в службу технической поддержки для получения помощи.

word_default:
When enabled, Friendly URLs will not include 'index.php'. In order to support this you must configure your web server to rewrite all URLs for your community directory to the index.php file. For assistance on how to do this, contact your hosting provider or system administrator.
To see the .htaccess used for Apache servers for comparison, download this file.
word_custom:
Если включено, то ЧПУ не будут включат в себя "index.php". Для корректной работы необходимо настроить ваш веб-сервер на перезапись всех ссылок вашего сайта, ведущих к файлу "index.php". Обратитесь к вашему системному администратору или хостинг-провайдеру для получения помощи.
Для просмотра .htaccess файла, используемого в Apache, скачайте этот файл.

word_default: It is strongly recommended to use friendly URLs as they are easier for both humans and search engine spiders to understand.
word_custom: Настоятельно рекомендуется использовать ЧПУ, поскольку они легче для понимания и людям, и поисковым роботам.

word_default:
When enabled, Friendly URLs will not include 'index.php'.
In order to support this you must download this file, upload it to your site's directory and rename it to '.htaccess' (with no file name). If there is already a .htaccess file, add the contents of this one to the existing.
If you are not sure how to do this, contact technical support for assistance.
word_custom:
Если включено, то ЧПУ не будут включат в себя "index.php".
Для работы этого вы должны скачать этот файл, загрузить его в директорию вашего сайта и переименовать в '.htaccess' (без названия файла). Если файл .htaccess существует, то необходимо добавить содержимое этого файла в существующий.
Если вы не уверены в совершаемых действиях, обратитесь к вашему хостинг-провайдеру.

word_default:
Friendly URLs are URLs that a human can look at and understand, as opposed to what may appear as an obscure string of text.
In addition to being more understandable to users, they help search engines understand better what is on each page.
word_custom:
ЧПУ отличаются от обычных ссылок тем, что пользователи могут понимать их т.к. они генерируются на основе заголовка категории, темы, записи и т.д.
Кроме того, они положительно влияют на отношение к вашему сайту со стороны поисковых систем.

Spam Defense is a service available to all clients who hold an active Invision Community license at no extra cost. When enabled, this service allows you to check new account registrations against our proprietary spammer database, helping to prevent spammers from registering on your site.

Настроить IPS Spam Service

word_default: Computer programs known as spam bots may attempt to register on your site to post unwanted content. CAPTCHA is a test designed to be simple for humans to answer correctly, but difficult for computer programs. The selected CAPTCHA type will display on the registration form of your site and will need to be completed successfully in order to register an account.
word_custom: Компьютерные программы, известные как спам-боты, могут попытаться зарегистрироваться на вашем сайте, чтобы добавить нежелательные публикации. CAPTCHA разработана таким способом, чтобы живому человеку было легко её пройти, но роботы не смогли этого сделать. Выбранный тип CAPTCHA будет отображаться на форме регистрации на сайте и пользователю будет необходимо пройти её, чтобы зарегистрироваться.

word_default: If enabled, an email will be sent to the site's incoming email address whenever a member of staff flags a member as a spammer.
word_custom: Если включено, на электронную почту сайта будет отправлено письмо при пометке пользователя спамером.

word_default: Be notified when a member is flagged?
Action to take when member is flagged

If a spam bot does manage to register on your site, the Flag as Spammer tool (available from members' profiles) allows staff to take the appropriate action. Hiding and deleting content is not done immediately but will be processed in batches.
If you later remove the flag, the actions are not reversed.
word_custom:
Если спам-боты зарегистрируются но вашем сайте, функция Пометить спамером (доступна в профиле пользователя) позволит администрации выполнить необходимые действия. Скрытие и удаление публикаций выполняется не мгновенно, а в фоновом режиме.
Если вы снимете у пользователя пометку спамером, предпринятые действия не будут отменены.
